oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Selections from two Eddy Arnold recording sessions - 1965-01-12 and 1965-01-13
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performances of Whatcha Gonna Do, What's He Doing In My World, Laura Lee, and Taking A Chance On Love. Performers include Eddy Arnold (vocals), Velma Williams (guitar), Wayne Moss (guitar), Harold Bradley (guitar), Henry Strzelecki (bass), Jerry Carrigan (drums), Floyd Cramer (piano), and Boots Randolph (sax). All songs were produced by Chet Atkins, and the first three songs were recorded on January 12, 1965, while the last song was recorded on January 13, 1965.
